m were, like me, the heads of a short list of obscure businesses. At a sing=
le-manager hedge fund things are a bit=C2=A0different:
=09There are probably only like a couple of dozen employees.=09Titles are p=
robably=C2=A0less important: There are fewer of you, and the job is less ab=
out marketing and more about results;=C2=A0most people would probably rathe=
r be called =E2=80=9Can analyst=E2=80=9D and get paid a lot than be called =
=E2=80=9Chead of consumer retail=E2=80=9D and be paid less.=09But there=E2=
=80=99s still some use for titles: You might get your due diligence calls r=
eturned quicker if you are the =E2=80=9Chead of consumer retail=E2=80=9D th=
an if you are just =E2=80=9Can analyst.=E2=80=9D=09Those titles can be gran=
ted at least as informally as they are at a bank: Your boss can say =E2=80=
=9Chere=E2=80=99s Matt, he=E2=80=99s the head of consumer retail,=E2=80=9D =
and who is going to disagree?=09Because there are fewer employees, the titl=
es can be bigger. Being the head of consumer retail at an investment bank i=
s a big job! There are a lot of investment bankers covering the consumer re=
