says the declaration; it appears to have effective governance control. =E2=
=80=9CAt the direction of Thai Union, Mr. Kenny became acting interim CEO f=
ollowing the resignation of the previous permanent CEO in April 2022,=E2=80=
=9D says a footnote in the declaration.


  [2] The idea here is presumably something like equitable subordination, a=
 bankruptcy doctrine designed =E2=80=9Cto prevent [corporate insiders] from=
 converting equity interests into claims or from improving the priority of =
their claims in anticipation of bankruptcy.=E2=80=9D My hypothetical trade =
at the beginning is, roughly, a way to convert equity interests into claims=
 (as a supplier), and if you can prove that the shareholder/supplier was do=
ing it intentionally then maybe you can claw back some money for creditors.


  [3] I feel like Greenlight is mostly known as a long/short equity fund, b=
ut it does do macro. Here=E2=80=99s a 2023 investor letter, noting 1.9% gro=
ss return from macro.


  [4] The rule is mostly that I need a =E2=80=9Clocate=E2=80=9D to do the s=
hort sale, that is, my broker needs to be pretty confident that I *can* bor=
row the shares by Wednesday. But I don=E2=80=99t need to actually borrow th=
e shares before doing the trade.


