<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is a hypothetical move:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You are in the business of producing =
and selling shrimp.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You expand ver=
tically by acquiring a chain of seafood restaurants.</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">The restaurants start to=C2=A0struggle and are heavily i=
ndebted, and you worry that your equity investment is losing value and poss=
ibly worthless.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">How to cut your lo=
sses?</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Well, you have two relations=
hips to the restaurant chain: You own the equity, and you also supply the s=
hrimp.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Not much you can do with th=
e equity: There=E2=80=99s a lot of debt, the creditors=C2=A0rank ahead of y=
ou, and they are unlikely to let you take any cash out as a dividend.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But, as the equity owner, you also con=
trol the board of directors and get to appoint the chief executive officer.=
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The CEO decides how much shrimp t=
o buy.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">What if he decided to buy a=
 <em>lot=C2=A0</em>of shrimp?</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Then=
 you=E2=80=99d make=C2=A0money on the shrimp, and extract at least some val=
ue out of your equity investment.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is presumably some tipping point.=C2=A0T=
here is some level where the restaurants are viable enough that you will wa=
nt to operate them to maximize their equity value, but if they fall below t=
hat level, you will give up on the equity=C2=A0and just try to maximize the=
 shrimp consumption. In the first equilibrium, you will spend money careful=
ly on=C2=A0shrimp and biscuits and silverware and advertising, with the goa=
l of increasing profitability. In the second equilibrium, you will spend mo=
ney profligately and only on shrimp, with the goal of spending money on shr=
imp.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CRed Lobster Chain Goes Bankrupt After=
 Unlimited Shrimp Deal=E2=80=9D is the great=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJ=
nLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMjAvc2VhZm9vZC1jaGFpbi1yZWQtbG9ic3Rlci=
1maWxlcy1mb3ItYmFua3J1cHRjeS1wcm90ZWN0aW9uLWx3ZWg3dHBqP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA1MjAyN=
F9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90=
ZXJtPTI0MDUyMCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB28b=
e5811" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">Bloomberg News headline</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Seafood restaurant chain Red Lobster filed for=
 bankruptcy, succumbing to onerous leases, high labor costs and a disastrou=
s unlimited shrimp promotion.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Orlando, Florida-based company filed for C=
hapter 11 protection on Sunday, listing assets and liabilities of $1 billio=
n to $10 billion each in its bankruptcy petition. The filing allows the com=
pany to keep operating while it works out a plan to repay creditors.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Red Lobster plans to hand control of the compa=
ny to its lenders, who have agreed to provide $100 million in financing to =
support the chain through bankruptcy.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly9kbS5lcGlxMTEuY29tL2Nhc2Uv=
cmVkbG9ic3Rlci9kb2NrZXRz/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB52d5db0e" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">bankrup=
tcy docket</a>, and here is yesterday=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly9kb2N1bWVudC5l=
cGlxMTEuY29tL2RvY3VtZW50L2dldGRvY3VtZW50Ynljb2RlP2RvY0lkPTQzMzQwMzYmcHJvamV=
jdENvZGU9UkxSJnNvdXJjZT1ETQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc7059529" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">firs=
t-day declaration</a> from Chief Executive officer Jonathan Tibus, a restru=
cturing expert who was appointed in March and who effectively works for the=
 creditors. Here he is on endless shrimp, and on the possible conflicts of =
interest of Red Lobster=E2=80=99s equity owner and supplier, Thai Union<a c=
lass=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpare=
nt !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Historically, the Debtors=E2=80=99 Ultimate En=
dless Shrimp (=E2=80=9CUES=E2=80=9D) promotion was utilized as a limited-ti=
me promotion. In May 2023, however, Paul Kenny, the Debtors=E2=80=99 former=
 CEO,=C2=A0made the decision to add UES as a permanent $20 item to the menu=
 despite significant pushback from other members of the Company=E2=80=99s m=
anagement team. This decision created both operational and financial issues=
 for the Debtors, costing the Debtors $11 million and saddling the Company =
with burdensome supply obligations, particularly with its equity sponsor, T=
hai Union. The Debtors are currently investigating the circumstances around=
 these decisions.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Debtors are also investigating whether Tha=
i Union and Mr. Kenny encouraged excessive merchandising of the UES promoti=
on in-store (including heavy in-store promotion), which was atypical for th=
e Company. The excessive merchandising decision led to supply issues result=
ing in major shortages of shrimp with restaurants often going days or weeks=
 without certain types of shrimp. Moreover, the Debtors are investigating w=
hether Mr. Kenny=E2=80=99s decision-making process circumvented the Company=
=E2=80=99s normal supply chain and demand planning processes.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Furthermore, I understand Red Lobster=E2=80=99=
s supply process was strained by virtue of its relationship with Thai Union=
, which, in addition to being the Company=E2=80=99s equity sponsor and 100%=
 owner of Red Lobster Master Holdings GP, has historically been a large-sca=
le supplier to=C2=A0Red Lobster. I understand that Thai Union exercised an =
outsized influence on the Company=E2=80=99s shrimp purchasing, as indicated=
 by, for example, Mr. Kenny=E2=80=99s April 2023 purported direction to Tha=
i Union to continue producing shrimp for Red Lobster that did not flow thro=
ugh the traditional supply process or bid cycle or adhere to the Company=E2=
=80=99s demand projections. I also understand that in apparent coordination=
 with Thai Union and under the guise of a =E2=80=9Cquality review,=E2=80=9D=
 Mr. Kenny made a series of decisions that eliminated two of the Company=E2=
=80=99s breaded shrimp suppliers, leaving Thai Union with an exclusive deal=
 that led to higher costs to Red Lobster.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Debtors are exploring the impact of the co=
ntrol Thai Union exerted, in concert with Mr. Kenny and other Thai Union-af=
filiated entities and individuals, and whether actions taken in light of th=
ese parties=E2=80=99 varying interests were appropriate and consistent with=
 applicable duties and obligations to Red Lobster.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I love my job, but would I take a sabbatical t=
o spend a few months on the team investigating whether Red Lobster=E2=80=99=
s controlling shareholder =E2=80=9Cexercised an outsized influence=E2=80=9D=
 on its shrimp purchasing and =E2=80=9Ccircumvented [its] normal supply cha=
in and demand planning processes=E2=80=9D? Probably. Someone has to get to =
the bottom of that shrimp merchandising.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Look: I think I am kidding.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CAs t=
o what drove Red Lobster to the edge, it=E2=80=99s clear that despite not b=
eing a very good idea, the blame doesn=E2=80=99t fall on Endless Shrimp,=E2=
=80=9D Business Insider=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnVzaW5lc3NpbnNpZGVyLmNvbS9=
yZWQtbG9ic3Rlci1lbmRsZXNzLXNocmltcC1iYW5rcnVwdGN5LXByaXZhdGUtZXF1aXR5LWRlYn=
QtcmVhbC1lc3RhdGUtMjAyNC01/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb85bca92" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Emily=
 Stewart argued</a> a few weeks ago. They didn=E2=80=99t send all the money=
=C2=A0out the door for shrimp. My assumption here is that the investigation=
 won=E2=80=99t find much,=C2=A0everyone was operating in good faith and doi=
ng the best job they could to save a struggling company, and at the start o=
f a bankruptcy you cast a wide net for possible ways to claw back money for=
 creditors.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-c=
olor: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0But what if that=E2=80=99s wrong?=C2=A0What if the executive meet=
ings were like:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>CEO:</strong> We=E2=80=99re in a lot o=
f trouble, any ideas?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Chief Financial Officer:</strong> Let=
=E2=80=99s close some underperforming locations and do a liability manageme=
nt exercise.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>CEO:</strong> I have a better idea. Sh=
rimp.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Chief Experience Officer:</strong> Wha=
t about shrimp in particular?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>CEO:</strong> I think we=C2=A0should b=
uy a ton of shrimp and then sell the heck out of them. I=E2=80=99m talking =
heavy in-store promotion, a permanent unlimited shrimp for $20 deal, maybe =
commission some songs about shrimp.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Chief Experience Officer:</strong>=C2=
=A0We actually have pretty detailed demand projections and they show that c=
ustomers only want =E2=80=94</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>CEO:</strong> Never mind the projectio=
ns, I am telling you, the answer is shrimp. We use every penny we have left=
 to buy shrimp, and the demand will follow!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Chief Experience Officer: </strong>...=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>CEO:</strong>=C2=A0Just bet the whole =
company on shrimp.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Chief Supply Chain Officer:</strong> O=
kay I guess we can bid out a huge new shrimp contract to suppliers.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>CEO:</strong> Oh no, no bids.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Then he gets up from the=C2=A0table and shrimp=
 fall out of his pockets and he=C2=A0walks out of the boardroom trailing sh=
rimp everywhere, this is what corporate finance is all about.</p>
<table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-content" width=3D"auto" cellpadding=3D=
"0" cellspacing=3D"0">
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"2" align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" style=3D"padding:0 0px">=20
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aH=
R0cHM6Ly9zbGkuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9jbGljaz9zPTg2ODQzMiZsaT0zNTQ0MDY5MCZtPTIxZ=
