<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Head of Macro</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlua=
W9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMTMvbmFrZWQtc2hvcnQtc2VsbGVyLWdldHMtaW4tdHJvdWJs=
ZT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNTIwMjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U=
9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA1MjAmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB2a65045c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">written before</a>, about my time at a=
n investment bank, that I was the head of a lot of businesses, and so was e=
veryone else:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Everyone is the head of something, or at least=
 co-head. Global Head of Cardboard Packaging Investment Banking, or America=
s Head of Exotic Volatility Trading in Stocks Starting with =E2=80=98P,=E2=
=80=99 or whatever. And many people are the head of two things, or three th=
ings, or most commonly an indeterminate number of things.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I cannot stress enough how important the head-=
of-something thing is. As a fairly junior vice president I would regularly =
go into client meetings with some senior relationship banker whom I had jus=
t met and who had no real idea of who I was, to talk about some weird deriv=
ative trade, and the banker would always introduce me to the client as like=
 =E2=80=9Cthis is Matt, he=E2=80=99s our global head of=E2=80=9D whatever t=
he weird trade was. =E2=80=A6 These headships were not, like, written down =
anywhere. No vote was taken, no corporate resolutions passed to make me the=
 head of whatever I was the head of that day. It was marketing: If a relati=
onship banker was taking me to pitch some weird thing to a client, then the=
 client would be happier and the relationship banker would be happier and I=
 would be happier if we all agreed that I was the bank=E2=80=99s leading ex=
pert and fully empowered manager of whatever weird thing I was pitching.</p=
>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I went on to add that some headships are prett=
y real: =E2=80=9CHead of Investment Banking=E2=80=9D is a real title that m=
atters. One way you know it matters=C2=A0is that a lot of investment banker=
s <em>report=C2=A0</em>to the head of investment banking; that person is an=
 actual boss. As head of whatever I was head of, I had one analyst, if I wa=
s lucky.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I worked at a big investment bank, with thousa=
nds of employees, many of whom were, like me, the heads of a short list of =
obscure businesses. At a single-manager hedge fund things are a bit=C2=A0di=
fferent:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There are probably only like a <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6=
Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvR3JlZW5saWdodF9DYXBpdGFs/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cBec780375" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;">couple of dozen</a> employees.</li>=09<li style=3D=
"margin-bottom: 5px;">Titles are probably=C2=A0less important: There are fe=
wer of you, and the job is less about marketing and more about results;=C2=
=A0most people would probably rather be called =E2=80=9Can analyst=E2=80=9D=
 and get paid a lot than be called =E2=80=9Chead of consumer retail=E2=80=
=9D and be paid less.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But there=E2=
=80=99s still <em>some </em>use for titles: You might get your due diligenc=
e calls returned quicker if you are the =E2=80=9Chead of consumer retail=E2=
=80=9D than if you are just =E2=80=9Can analyst.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Those titles can be granted at least as informally=
 as they are at a bank: Your boss can say =E2=80=9Chere=E2=80=99s Matt, he=
=E2=80=99s the head of consumer retail,=E2=80=9D and who is going to disagr=
ee?</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Because there are fewer employ=
ees, the titles can be <em>bigger</em>. Being the head of consumer retail a=
t an investment bank is a big job! There are a lot of investment bankers co=
vering the consumer retail sector, and they all report to you; a lot of peo=
ple would like to be the head of consumer retail but only one person (maybe=
 two) gets to be it. At a hedge fund with a dozen analysts, probably each a=
nalyst will have her own fairly large coverage universe. If you=E2=80=99re =
the analyst covering consumer retail companies, then you are also the =E2=
=80=9Chead of consumer retail.=E2=80=9D Who else could it be? You are the h=
ead of a team of one, but that=E2=80=99s a pretty common experience in the =
financial industry.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sorry! None of this is very important! But I c=
annot <em>not </em>mention James Fishback and Greenlight Capital Inc., who =
are <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35440690.28534=
0/aHR0cHM6Ly9zaGVyd29vZC5uZXdzL2J1c2luZXNzL2dyZWVubGlnaHQtY2FwaXRhbC1pbi1sZ=
WdhbC1iYXR0bGUtd2l0aC1qYW1lcy1maXNoYmFuay1hLWZvcm1lci1lbXBsb3llZS8/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cB787c0fc5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">suing each other</a>=C2=A0about whether =
or not Fishback was Greenlight=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Chead of macro.=E2=80=9D<a=
 class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpa=
rent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0h=
CRmRmeElVL3JHUFpEMUNmSW9aRS92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd625222b" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
Fishback=E2=80=99s lawsuit</a> from last October, saying that he was:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Fishback was previously employed by Greenl=
ight, beginning as a research analyst, then as a trader, and finally as its=
 Head of Macro. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Greenlight repeatedly confirmed, both in writi=
ng and verbally, that Mr. Fishback was Greenlight=E2=80=99s Head of Macro.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For example, on May 11, 2023, [Greenlight Chie=
f Operating Officer Daniel] Roitman, in securing an invitation for Mr. Fish=
back to join a private call with Dr. Eric S. Rosengren, former president of=
 the Federal Reserve Bank of Boston, emailed Heather Robertson, a Senior Ma=
nager of the GLG Group the following: =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CHeather =E2=80=94 can you sign James =
Fishback for this? He=E2=80=99s our head of macro here. Copying him to the =
email.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In addition to this email from Roitman directl=
y stating that Mr. Fishback was Greenlight=E2=80=99s Head of Macro, the tit=
le had been communicated to Mr. Fishback and others numerous times, includi=
ng when he was introduced by Greenlight employees at conferences, dinners, =
and on calls.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pb=
y9kb2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3I2MWtlRVo1bkoxay92MA/607f07ceef4b8=
524a319a23cB5202b83b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">Greenlight=E2=80=99s lawsuit</a> from March, =
saying that he wasn=E2=80=99t:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Greenlight received information su=
ggesting that Defendant had falsely represented himself as having held cert=
ain titles during his employment with Greenlight other than =E2=80=9CResear=
ch Analyst,=E2=80=9D including but not limited to =E2=80=9CHead of Macro,=
=E2=80=9D and upon information and belief, falsely represented his role in =
Greenlight=E2=80=99s investment performance. Greenlight became aware of the=
se false representations through Defendant=E2=80=99s efforts to market hims=
elf and a hedge fund that he had founded, Azoria Partners, to potential inv=
estors. Greenlight understood that Defendant was using the =E2=80=9CHead of=
 Macro=E2=80=9D title to wrongfully appropriate Greenlight=E2=80=99s track =
record and success in making investments informed by macroeconomic events (=
referred to as =E2=80=9Cmacro=E2=80=9D investing or trading). These represe=
ntations were false because the purported =E2=80=9CHead of Macro=E2=80=9D t=
itle has never existed at Greenlight, and had not been given to Defendant.<=
/p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Some of the most gloriously petty stuff you wi=
ll ever see in investment management. Here is an <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9nZWlnZXJf=
Y2FwaXRhbC9zdGF0dXMvMTc5MTIzMjY2ODM1ODU5ODgyNQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd5c=
5d54f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">email exchange</a> between Roitman and Fishback, in which Fi=
shback says =E2=80=9CI will not be compelled to lie,=E2=80=9D and Roitman r=
eplies =E2=80=9CCompelled to lie? What are you talking about?=E2=80=9D Here=
 is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35440690.28534=
0/aHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9qX2Zpc2hiYWNr/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8aa5d879" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;">Fishback=E2=80=99s X account</a>, where he posts memes about being the h=
ead of macro and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
5440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9qX2Zpc2hiYWNrL3N0YXR1cy8xNzkxMDczMzU4ODUy=
NzkyNDQ3/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB85b12345" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">tries to debate</a> Gre=
enlight boss David Einhorn about Tesla.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fishback=E2=80=99s complaint says that he had =
a lot of responsibility at Greenlight, including making trades with its cap=
ital, but it does not seem to mention how many <em>other </em>people were o=
n the macro team that he headed. I have a guess! Anyway I assume both sides=
 are right: Surely Greenlight did not have a =E2=80=9Chead of macro,=E2=80=
=9D and surely Greenlight did go around saying that=C2=A0Fishback was it.</=
p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">T+1ish</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way it works now is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">On Monday, we do a stock trade: I agr=
ee to sell you 100 shares of XYZ for $20 each.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-b=
ottom: 5px;">On Wednesday, we settle the trade: I give you the 100 shares, =
and you give me the $2,000.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">That g=
ives me <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35440690.2=
85340/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDItM=
jgvdHJhZGluZy1zdG9jay10YWtlcy10aW1lP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA1MjAyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0=
bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDUyMCZ1dG1=
fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa50fed8c" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">two =
days to find the shares</a>. Probably=C2=A0I already had them on Monday, bu=
t maybe not. Maybe I was doing a short sale, and I need to arrange to borro=
w the shares between Monday and Wednesday.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=
=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inli=
ne-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a> Or maybe I was doing a long sale, but I had=C2=A0loaned<em>=C2=A0</em>=
my shares to someone else, and now I need to call them back.</li>=09<li sty=
le=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">And you have two=C2=A0days to find the money. Ma=
ybe=C2=A0you already had the money in your brokerage account on Monday, but=
 maybe not. Maybe you need to move money from a bank account. Maybe you nee=
d to get a margin loan from your broker. Maybe your money is in euros and y=
ou need to convert it into dollars.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;=
">Almost all of the time, this works out fine: I get the stock, you get the=
 money, we meet up on Wednesday and exchange them.</li>=09<li style=3D"marg=
in-bottom: 5px;">Every so often, we run out of time: I recall my stock loan=
 but the borrower doesn=E2=80=99t return the shares in time, or your bank c=
loses early and you can=E2=80=99t move the money in time.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">In that case =E2=80=A6 we settle the trade on Thur=
sday? Maybe Friday? Ehh. Mistakes happen. This is called a =E2=80=9Csettlem=
ent fail,=E2=80=9D and it=E2=80=99s not=C2=A0<em>great</em>, you know, but =
mostly everyone survives. Not always. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXd=
zL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMTkvbmV3LXQtMS1ydWxlLWlzLXNwZWVkaW5nLXVwLXNldHRsZW=
1lbnQtdGltZS1hbmQtd2FsbC1zdHJlZXQtaXMtd29ycmllZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNTIwMjRfTU9OR=
VlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0y=
NDA1MjAmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB79c705e2" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;">Fails</a> =E2=80=9Ccan result in regulatory punishment, loss of cap=
ital tied up in the trade, and even =E2=80=94 in very rare instances when t=
he transaction is large enough =E2=80=94 the collapse of parties in the dea=
l.=E2=80=9D Also they <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGV=
zLzIwMjQtMDQtMjIvdGhlLXNlY3JldC10cmFkZS13YXMtb3B0aW9ucy1pbi1pbmRpYT9jbXBpZD=
1CQkQwNTIwMjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xld=
HRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA1MjAmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cBcf3bd982" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">make Devin Nunes angry</a>.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway that system is called T+2 settlement, b=
ecause trades settle two days after the trade date. Next week the US will m=
ove to T+1 settlement. That is the same as the above, except:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">We settle on Tuesday instead of Wedne=
sday.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">This gives you one less day =
to find the cash, and me one less day to find the stock.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">We will run out of time more often, especially in =
the beginning, when we are less used to doing stuff this fast.</li>=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">In that case =E2=80=A6=C2=A0probably we settle=
 on Wednesday? Mistakes happen. This will be more embarrassing on a systemi=
c level =E2=80=94=C2=A0everyone is practicing real hard to settle trades T+=
1, and will be paying attention to the transition=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0but l=
ess embarrassing on an individual level, because of course everyone is goin=
g to mess it up sometimes.=C2=A0</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Roughly speaking, moving from T+2 to T+1 settl=
ement means something more like moving from T+2.001 settlement to, like, T+=
1.05=C2=A0settlement. Most trades settle faster, but a larger minority don=
=E2=80=99t. Bloomberg=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2Fyd=
GljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMTkvbmV3LXQtMS1ydWxlLWlzLXNwZWVkaW5nLXVwLXNldHRsZW1lbnQt=
dGltZS1hbmQtd2FsbC1zdHJlZXQtaXMtd29ycmllZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNTIwMjRfTU9ORVlTVFV=
GRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA1Mj=
AmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC79c705e2" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">Greg Ritchie reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When US markets reopen next Tuesday after the =
long weekend, everything will likely seem normal. It=E2=80=99s only after t=
he close and in the following days that any cracks are expected to appear.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A spike in the number of failed trades, operat=
ional glitches and additional costs are among industry fears as the trading=
 process for American securities accelerates, with the time allowed to comp=
lete every transaction halved to a single day. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThere=E2=80=99s a lot of anxiety even=
 just around the technology and the actual way by which settlement will tak=
e place,=E2=80=9D Amy Hong, head of market structure and strategic partners=
hips for global banking and markets at Goldman Sachs Group, told the Bloomb=
erg Sell-Side Leaders Forum this month. =E2=80=9CThere are going to be some=
 mismatches around funding, there are going to be some FX-related issues th=
at we=E2=80=99re going to need to work out.=E2=80=9D ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Just 9% of sell-side firms polled by Coalition=
 Greenwich in April and May said they expect the T+1 switch to go smoothly,=
 with 38% warning that buy-side managers are unprepared, and 28% believing =
trading platforms aren=E2=80=99t fully ready. Almost a fifth anticipate a l=
arge disruption with =E2=80=9Cmany or severe issues.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The consensus view is that trade failures =E2=
=80=94 when either a seller doesn=E2=80=99t deliver securities or a buyer f=
ails to produce payment =E2=80=94 are about to rise. The question is how la=
rge and persistent that uptick will be. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The $7.5 trillion-a-day foreign-exchange marke=
t is a flashpoint of the shift, because currency trades typically settle on=
 a T+2 basis. An overseas investor buying a US stock will soon need to eith=
er have dollars ready or find them within a day in an arena where it can ta=
ke two.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s worth wondering what =E2=80=9Cman=
y or severe issues=E2=80=9D could mean. Like two possible categories of =E2=
=80=9Csevere issues=E2=80=9D would be:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The stock market will stop functioning=
, trades that are agreed will never settle, and major financial institution=
s will be bankrupted by the chaos.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;"=
>The person at the sell-side firm who is answering the Coalition Greenwich =
settlement-mechanics survey will get yelled at a lot more over the next mon=
th than she was over the prior month.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Those both probably=C2=A0<em>feel=C2=A0</em>se=
vere.=C2=A0</p>
