<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2=
FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDUtMTYvY3J5cHRvLWJyb3RoZXJzLWZyb250LXJhbi10aGUtZnJvbnQtc=
nVubmVycz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNTIwMjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9z=
b3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA1MjAmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcead8ade" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">wrote last Thursday</a> about t=
wo brothers who were charged with wire fraud for doing an exploit on the Et=
hereum blockchain that allegedly earned them $25 million from arbitrage bot=
s. Ordinarily here is where I would give a two-sentence summary of the stor=
y, but honestly it is complicated, and I would advise you to either (1) rea=
d what I wrote last week or (2) skip the rest of this section.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are still here, though, I want to clari=
fy two points based on emails I got from readers.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">First, though I described the exploit as =E2=
=80=9Cfront-running the front-runners,=E2=80=9D I do want to be clear that =
it was<em>=C2=A0</em>not=C2=A0<em>just</em>=C2=A0that. This is not a=C2=A0<=
em>pure=C2=A0</em>case of (1) submitting spoofy orders to bait=C2=A0front-r=
unning bots, (2) having them take the bait and (3) finding some trade to ma=
ke them lose money. (There=C2=A0<em>are=C2=A0</em><a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly9naXRodWIuY29tL0R=
lZmktQ2FydGVsL3NhbG1vbmVsbGE/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB38865f31" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">pri=
or examples of that</a>, using oddly structured tokens to make the front-ru=
nners lose money.) Here, though, the brothers are accused of something clos=
er to hacking, exploiting a weakness in software code to be able to see (an=
d reorder) a series of transactions that was supposed to be kept confidenti=
al from them. That=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>worse; it=E2=80=99s sort of like t=
he difference between (1) putting in spoof orders on the stock exchange to =
try to trick a high-frequency trading firm and (2) hacking into the stock e=
xchange=E2=80=99s computer system to reverse the HFT firm=E2=80=99s trades.=
 Even if you think that the front-running bots are bad, you might =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0as the Justice Department does =E2=80=94=C2=A0object to this approach=
 to punishing them.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Second, I said that =E2=80=9Cthey exploited a =
bug in Ethereum=E2=80=9D to do this, but that=E2=80=99s not quite right. Th=
ey exploited a bug in Flashbots=E2=80=99 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly9kb2NzLmZsYXNoYm90cy5uZXQv=
Zmxhc2hib3RzLW1ldi1ib29zdC9pbnRyb2R1Y3Rpb24/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd90079=
38" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">MEV-Boost</a>, open-source block-building software <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3YvdXNhby1zZG55L21lZGlhLzEzNTE5MzEvZGw/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB93f8220f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">that</a> =E2=80=9Capproximately 90% of Ethereum vali=
dators use=E2=80=9D but that is not part of the core Ethereum system itself=
. (Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3544069=
0.285340/aHR0cHM6Ly9jb2xsZWN0aXZlLmZsYXNoYm90cy5uZXQvdC9wb3N0LW1vcnRlbS1hcH=
JpbC0zcmQtMjAyMy1tZXYtYm9vc3QtcmVsYXktaW5jaWRlbnQtYW5kLXJlbGF0ZWQtdGltaW5nL=
Wlzc3VlLzE1NDA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBde7726d6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Flashbots=E2=80=
=99 explanation</a>.) They exploited a bug in how blocks are normally built=
 and proposed on Ethereum. From the names =E2=80=9CFlashbots=E2=80=9D and =
=E2=80=9CMEV-Boost,=E2=80=9D though, you might get some sense of why the ca=
se is controversial. The way that blocks are normally built and proposed on=
 Ethereum involves =E2=80=9Cmaximal extractable value=E2=80=9D (MEV), where=
 arbitrage traders bid to pay validators for priority to make the most prof=
itable trades. These brothers hacked=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>system, but no=
t everyone likes that system, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusines=
s.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0cDovL2FyeGl2Lm9yZy9wZGYvMTkwNC4wNTIzNA/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcbeb57dd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">because it involves</a> predatory tr=
aders front-running more naive traders.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is also important because, as one reader =
commented: =E2=80=9CA=C2=A0a crucial distinguishing factor here is that Jam=
es and Anton did not re-order=C2=A0committed=C2=A0transactions; they instea=
d picked an ordering of=C2=A0pending=C2=A0transactions that were favorable =
to them. Under this lens, the integrity of the blockchain is not compromise=
d; the network explicitly =E2=80=98allows=E2=80=99 validators to pick whate=
ver arbitrary ordering of transactions they like; it's just that generally =
it=E2=80=99s economically favorable for validators to prioritize transactio=
ns which pay them the most first.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere, here is a good and balanced=C2=A0<a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35440690.285340/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cuY29pbmRlc2suY29tL29waW5pb24vMjAyNC8wNS8xNS93aGF0LXRoZS1kb2pzLWZ=
pcnN0LW1ldi1sYXdzdWl0LW1lYW5zLWZvci1ldGhlcmV1bS9hbXAv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cB0c2893e8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">CoinDesk article</a> about why this case is controver=
sial:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">MEV, which itself is controversial, can be a h=
ighly lucrative game dominated by automated bots that often comes at blockc=
hain users=E2=80=99 expense, which is partially why so many in the crypto c=
ommunity have rushed to denounce the DOJ=E2=80=99s complaint. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThey used a flaw in MEV boost to push=
 invalid signatures to preview bundles. That gives an unfair advantage via =
an exploit,=E2=80=9D former employee of the Ethereum Foundation and Flashbo=
ts Hudson Jameson told CoinDesk in an interview. Jameson added that the Per=
aire-Bueno brothers were also running their own validator while extracting =
MEV, which violates something of a gentleman=E2=80=99s agreement in MEV cir=
cles.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CNo one else in the MEV ecosystem was =
doing both of those things at once that we know of,=E2=80=9D he added. =E2=
=80=9CThey did more than just play by both the codified and pinky promise r=
ules of MEV extraction.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt's not some kind of robin hood stor=
y as they didn't return the money to people MEVers extracted it from,=E2=80=
=9D pseudonymous researcher Banteg said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well, no, they=E2=80=99re not going to=C2=A0<e=
m>return=C2=A0</em>the money.</p>
